full_text: The faces in my undergrad program are changing and I know some of the people who weren't there when I was a student are doing great things. And I did love so many of my professors and probably looked up to them too much to the point I am still writing for them.
full_text(utf-8): b"The faces in my undergrad program are changing and I know some of the people who weren't there when I was a student are doing great things. And I did love so many of my professors and probably looked up to them too much to the point I am still writing for them."

full_text: Ball State grad school was a difficult time for me but I am thankful that the department had a greater openness as to what a story could be and encouraged experimentation. I never got the "no, you can't do that. Now read my food poetry" attitude there.
full_text(utf-8): b'Ball State grad school was a difficult time for me but I am thankful that the department had a greater openness as to what a story could be and encouraged experimentation. I never got the "no, you can\'t do that. Now read my food poetry" attitude there.'

full_text: I had much more fun writing before college than I did afterwards. I was much more productive, too. I'm thankful for my intro to journalism and nonfiction but I miss being able to write without feeling like a professor is looking over my shoulder and judging me.
full_text(utf-8): b"I had much more fun writing before college than I did afterwards. I was much more productive, too. I'm thankful for my intro to journalism and nonfiction but I miss being able to write without feeling like a professor is looking over my shoulder and judging me."

full_text: I value everything I learned in undergrad (and grad) and I know it's important to learn those basics from the 200 level beginner classes (which is why I say a 300-400 level class), but I walked away with a dead imagination.
